text: Ylöjärvi is a town in Pirkanmaa, Finland. As of 28 February 2023, 33,597 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Hämeenkyrö, Ikaalinen, Kihniö, Nokia, Parkano, Ruovesi, Tampere and Virrat. The former municipality of Viljakkala was merged with Ylöjärvi on 1 January 2007. The former municipality of Kuru was merged with Ylöjärvi on 1 January 2009. == Other websites == * Town of Ylöjärvi – Official website Category:Municipalities of Pirkanmaa
